methods.clear:
Set the SSM at the specified key to null

:param key: (long) - the key to get the ssm for.
methods.clearDeltas:
Clear out any tracked deltas from recent computations.

:param indices: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.Index) - the set of indices to clear deltas for.
methods.ensureCapacity:
Ensure the source has at least `capacity` capacity

:param capacity: (long) - the capacity to ensure.
methods.getCurrentSsm:
Get the current SSM at the specified key. This does not permute it in any way.

:param key: (long) - the key to get the ssm for.
:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.ssms.CharSegmentedSortedMultiset) the SSM
methods.getOrCreate:
Get the ssm at the specified key, creating one if none existed.  This method will
 update the current previous tracking state of the SSM.

:param key: (long) - the key to get the ssm for.
:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.ssms.CharSegmentedSortedMultiset) the SSM at the key, or a new one.
methods.isImmutable:
Determine if this column source is immutable, meaning that the values at a given index key never change.

:return: (boolean) true if the values at a given index of the column source never change, false otherwise
methods.startTrackingPrevValues:
ColumnSource implementations that track previous values have the option to not actually start tracking previous
 values until this method is called. This is an option, not an obligation: some simple ColumnSource
 implementations (like TSingleValueSource for various T) always track previous values; other implementations (like
 PrevColumnSource) never do; some (like TArrayColumnSource) only start tracking once this method is called.

 An immutable column source can not have distinct prev values; therefore it is implemented as a no-op.
